## MVP Phase - Design System & Foundations

### Epic: DS-001 - Design System & Component Library

#### Story DS-001.1: Core Design System Foundation

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** create a comprehensive design system with typography, color palette, spacing, and grid system,  
**So that** the entire application has a consistent visual language that reflects music culture while ensuring usability.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 5 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am establishing the design foundation,  
**When** I create the design system documentation,  
**Then** it must include:
- Primary and secondary color palettes with accessibility ratios (WCAG 2.1 AA compliant)
- Typography scale (headings H1-H6, body text, captions) with font families
- Spacing system (4px base grid with 8px, 16px, 24px, 32px, 48px, 64px increments)
- Grid system (12-column responsive grid with breakpoints)
- Elevation and shadow system (4 levels)
- Border radius system (0px, 4px, 8px, 16px, full rounded)
- Icon library selection (minimum 50 common icons)

**Given** I am ensuring brand alignment,  
**When** I design the color palette,  
**Then** it must:
- Feature a bold primary color that evokes music energy (e.g., electric blue, rock red, metal black)
- Include neutral grays for content hierarchy
- Define semantic colors for success, warning, error, and info states
- Provide dark mode alternatives for all colors
- Pass WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratios for text on backgrounds (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)

**Design Deliverables**:
- Figma/Sketch design system library with all tokens
- Design system documentation (PDF or web page)
- Color palette with hex/RGB values and usage guidelines
- Typography specimen sheet with examples
- Spacing and grid documentation with examples
- Icon library with naming conventions

**Technical Notes**:
- Design tokens should be exportable to CSS variables and JSON
- Consider Ant Design 5+ as base component library with customization
- Use system fonts as fallback (system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont)
- Minimum touch target size: 44px x 44px (iOS HIG, WCAG)

---

#### Story DS-001.2: Component Library Design

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** design a reusable component library covering all common UI patterns,  
**So that** developers can implement consistent, accessible interfaces efficiently.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 8 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am creating the component library,  
**When** I design the components,  
**Then** I must include at minimum:
- Buttons (primary, secondary, tertiary, text, icon, sizes, states)
- Form inputs (text, email, password, number, textarea, dropdown, checkbox, radio)
- Cards (product card, info card, stat card)
- Navigation (header, footer, breadcrumbs, pagination)
- Alerts and notifications (success, warning, error, info)
- Modals and dialogs
- Badges and tags
- Loading states (spinners, skeletons, progress bars)
- Empty states with illustrations
- Error states with guidance
- Tooltips and popovers

**Given** I am ensuring accessibility,  
**When** I design each component,  
**Then** it must:
- Show all interactive states (default, hover, focus, active, disabled, error, loading)
- Include keyboard focus indicators (visible 2px outline)
- Provide clear visual hierarchy
- Support screen reader requirements (labeled appropriately)
- Meet minimum touch/click target sizes (44px x 44px)

**Given** I am supporting responsive design,  
**When** I create component variants,  
**Then** I must provide:
- Desktop layouts (1440px, 1920px)
- Tablet layouts (768px, 1024px)
- Mobile layouts (375px, 414px)
- Responsive behavior documentation

**Design Deliverables**:
- Complete Figma/Sketch component library with variants
- Component usage documentation with do's and don'ts
- Accessibility annotations for developers
- Responsive behavior guidelines
- Component interaction states documentation
- Code handoff specifications (measurements, colors, typography)

**Technical Notes**:
- Base on Ant Design 5+ components with custom theming
- Ensure components are themeable for potential dark mode
- Document component props and configurations for React implementation

