### Epic: DS-002 - Information Architecture & User Flows

#### Story DS-002.1: Site Information Architecture

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** define the complete site structure and navigation hierarchy,  
**So that** users can easily find products and complete tasks with minimal friction.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 3 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am structuring the site navigation,  
**When** I create the information architecture,  
**Then** I must define:
- Primary navigation structure (Home, Shop, Categories, About, Account)
- Category hierarchy (8 music genres as top-level categories)
- Footer navigation (Customer Service, Company Info, Legal, Social)
- User account section structure (Profile, Orders, Addresses, Wishlist in Phase 1)
- Admin dashboard structure (Dashboard, Products, Orders, Customers, Analytics)
- Breadcrumb navigation patterns
- Mobile navigation patterns (hamburger menu or bottom navigation)

**Given** I am optimizing for user personas,  
**When** I design the navigation,  
**Then** it must:
- Provide quick access to "New Arrivals" and "Trending" for Alex (passionate fan)
- Feature prominent search bar for Jamie (casual shopper)
- Include "Gift Guide" in navigation for Morgan (gift buyer)
- Support keyboard navigation (Tab, Arrow keys)

**Design Deliverables**:
- Site map diagram showing all pages and relationships
- Navigation hierarchy documentation
- Breadcrumb pattern examples
- Mobile navigation design mockups
- Search functionality specifications

---

#### Story DS-002.2: Key User Flow Mapping

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** map out critical user journeys from entry to completion,  
**So that** I can identify and eliminate friction points in the user experience.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 3 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am documenting user journeys,  
**When** I create user flow diagrams,  
**Then** I must map:
- Guest user flow: Landing → Browse → Product Detail → Add to Cart → Guest Checkout → Order Confirmation
- Registered user flow: Login → Browse → Add to Cart → Checkout (saved info) → Order Confirmation
- Admin flow: Login → Dashboard → Manage Products → Update Inventory → View Orders
- Product discovery flow: Search → Filter/Sort → Product Detail → Related Products
- Order tracking flow: Order History → Order Details → Track Shipment
- Password reset flow: Forgot Password → Email → Reset Link → New Password → Success

**Given** I am optimizing conversion,  
**When** I design the checkout flow,  
**Then** it must:
- Minimize steps (cart → shipping → payment → confirmation = 4 screens max)
- Show progress indicator
- Allow editing of previous steps without losing data
- Provide guest checkout option prominently
- Display order summary throughout

**Design Deliverables**:
- User flow diagrams for all critical paths
- Screen-to-screen transition documentation
- Friction point analysis with solutions
- Conversion optimization recommendations
- Error recovery flow designs

---

## MVP Phase - User Interface Components

### Epic: UI-001 - Authentication & User Profile

#### Story UI-001.1: Registration & Login Interface

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** design intuitive registration and login screens,  
**So that** users can easily create accounts and access their profiles with minimal friction.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 2 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am designing the registration page,  
**When** a user wants to create an account,  
**Then** the interface must:
- Display a clear, centered registration form with email and password fields
- Show real-time password strength indicator
- Include inline validation with helpful error messages
- Provide "Already have an account? Login" link
- Show privacy policy and terms of service agreement checkbox
- Display clear "Create Account" button (primary CTA)
- Show success state and "Check your email for verification" message

**Given** I am designing the login page,  
**When** a user wants to sign in,  
**Then** the interface must:
- Display email and password fields with appropriate input types
- Include "Remember me" checkbox
- Show "Forgot password?" link prominently
- Provide clear error states for invalid credentials
- Display "Don't have an account? Register" link
- Include social login options placeholders (Phase 3)

**Given** I am ensuring accessibility,  
**When** users interact with forms,  
**Then** the design must:
- Show clear focus indicators on all form fields
- Provide appropriate ARIA labels and error announcements
- Support password visibility toggle
- Enable keyboard navigation (Tab, Enter)
- Display clear loading states during submission

**Design Deliverables**:
- Registration page mockups (desktop, tablet, mobile)
- Login page mockups (desktop, tablet, mobile)
- Email verification success screen
- Form validation state designs (error, success, loading)
- Interaction states documentation
- Responsive layout specifications

---

#### Story UI-001.2: Password Reset Flow

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** design a clear password reset process,  
**So that** users can securely recover their accounts without confusion or frustration.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 1 story point

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am designing the password reset flow,  
**When** a user needs to reset their password,  
**Then** I must design:
- "Forgot Password" page with email input and clear instructions
- "Email Sent" confirmation screen with next steps
- Password reset form (from email link) with new password and confirm fields
- Password reset success screen with "Login Now" CTA
- Expired link error screen with option to request new link

**Design Deliverables**:
- Password reset flow screens (all states)
- Email template design for reset link
- Error state designs
- Success confirmation designs

---

#### Story UI-001.3: User Profile Management Interface

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** design an intuitive profile management interface,  
**So that** users can easily view and update their personal information and preferences.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 2 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am designing the user profile page,  
**When** a logged-in user accesses their profile,  
**Then** the interface must display:
- User information section (name, email, phone number) with edit functionality
- Shipping addresses management (add, edit, delete, set default)
- Password change section (current password, new password, confirm)
- Account preferences (email notifications, newsletter)
- Order history summary with link to full history
- Wishlist quick access (Phase 1)
- Logout button

**Given** I am optimizing for usability,  
**When** users edit their information,  
**Then** the design must:
- Use inline editing or modal dialogs for updates
- Show clear save/cancel actions
- Display success confirmations for updates
- Provide validation feedback in real-time
- Support multiple saved shipping addresses

**Design Deliverables**:
- User profile page mockups (desktop, tablet, mobile)
- Edit profile modal/inline editing states
- Address management interface
- Password change interface
- Success and error state designs

