### Epic: UI-002 - Product Catalog & Discovery

#### Story UI-002.1: Homepage Design

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** design an engaging homepage that showcases products and guides users to relevant content,  
**So that** users are inspired to browse and can quickly find what they're looking for.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 3 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am designing the homepage,  
**When** a user lands on the site,  
**Then** the interface must include:
- Hero section with bold imagery and primary CTA (e.g., "Shop New Arrivals")
- Featured categories section (8 genre tiles with images)
- "New Arrivals" product carousel/grid (8-12 products)
- "Trending Now" section highlighting popular items
- "Shop by Band" quick links to popular artists
- Email newsletter signup form (footer or modal)
- Social proof elements (e.g., "Join 10,000+ music fans")

**Given** I am optimizing for conversion,  
**When** I design the hero section,  
**Then** it must:
- Feature high-quality lifestyle imagery showing T-shirts in context
- Display clear, action-oriented headline
- Include prominent search bar or "Shop Now" CTA
- Support image/content rotation for promotional campaigns
- Be responsive and performant on all devices

**Given** I am supporting different user personas,  
**When** I layout the homepage sections,  
**Then** I must:
- Make "New Arrivals" prominent for Alex (passionate fan)
- Feature clear category navigation for Jamie (casual shopper)
- Include "Gift Guide" or "Popular Picks" for Morgan (gift buyer)
- Ensure fast load time with optimized images (<2 seconds)

**Design Deliverables**:
- Homepage desktop mockup (1440px)
- Homepage mobile mockup (375px)
- Hero section variations (3-4 examples)
- Category tile designs
- Product carousel/grid layouts
- Hover states and interactions
- Responsive behavior documentation

---

#### Story UI-002.2: Product Listing Page Design

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** design an efficient product listing page with filtering and sorting,  
**So that** users can browse large catalogs and narrow down choices quickly.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 3 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am designing the product listing page,  
**When** a user browses a category or search results,  
**Then** the interface must include:
- Breadcrumb navigation showing current location
- Page title (category name or search query)
- Filtering sidebar (desktop) or drawer (mobile) with:
  - Genre/Category
  - Size (XS, S, M, L, XL, XXL)
  - Color swatches
  - Price range slider
  - Availability (In Stock, On Sale)
- Active filters display with clear remove options
- Sort dropdown (Newest, Price: Low to High, Price: High to Low, Popular)
- Product grid (3-4 columns desktop, 2 columns tablet, 1-2 columns mobile)
- Results count (e.g., "Showing 1-24 of 156 results")
- Pagination or infinite scroll
- View toggle (grid/list view - optional)

**Given** I am designing product cards,  
**When** displayed in the grid,  
**Then** each card must show:
- Product image with hover state (show second image or zoom)
- Band name
- Product name/description
- Price (with sale price if applicable)
- Available sizes indicator
- "Add to Cart" button (appears on hover on desktop)
- Wishlist heart icon (Phase 1)
- "Quick View" option (optional)
- Out of stock badge if unavailable
- "New" or "Trending" badge if applicable

**Given** I am optimizing for mobile,  
**When** users browse on small screens,  
**Then** the design must:
- Use collapsible filter drawer accessible via "Filter" button
- Stack product cards in 2 columns (or 1 for very small screens)
- Make sort and filter easily accessible
- Support touch interactions
- Load images lazily for performance

**Design Deliverables**:
- Product listing page mockups (desktop, tablet, mobile)
- Filter sidebar/drawer designs (open and closed states)
- Product card component (multiple states: default, hover, out of stock)
- Sort dropdown designs
- Active filters display
- Pagination design
- Empty state design ("No products found")
- Loading state (skeleton screens)

---

#### Story UI-002.3: Product Detail Page Design

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** design a comprehensive product detail page that provides all necessary information,  
**So that** users can make confident purchase decisions.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 3 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am designing the product detail page,  
**When** a user views a product,  
**Then** the interface must include:
- Image gallery (main image + 3-5 thumbnails, zoomable, lightbox)
- Product name (prominent, H1)
- Band name (linked to band's products)
- Price (large, clear, with sale price if applicable)
- Product rating stars and review count (Phase 1: functional, MVP: placeholder)
- Size selector (visual buttons: XS, S, M, L, XL, XXL)
- Color selector (color swatches if multiple colors available)
- Quantity selector (- 1 + buttons, max 10)
- "Add to Cart" primary CTA button (prominent)
- "Add to Wishlist" secondary button (Phase 1)
- Stock availability indicator ("In Stock", "Only 3 left", "Out of Stock")
- Product description (rich text with formatting)
- Size guide link (opens modal with sizing chart)
- Material and care instructions (expandable section)
- Shipping information (expandable section)
- Return policy (expandable section)
- Share buttons (social media)
- Related products section (4-6 products)
- Customer reviews section (Phase 1)

**Given** I am optimizing for conversion,  
**When** I design the add-to-cart section,  
**Then** it must:
- Keep CTA visible on scroll (sticky on mobile)
- Show clear validation messages if size not selected
- Display loading state when adding to cart
- Show success confirmation (toast or modal)
- Provide "View Cart" or "Continue Shopping" options after adding

**Given** I am supporting mobile users,  
**When** users view the page on small screens,  
**Then** the design must:
- Stack image gallery above product info
- Make size/color selectors easily tappable (min 44px)
- Sticky "Add to Cart" button at bottom of screen
- Collapsible accordion sections for details
- Optimized image gallery for touch (swipe gestures)

**Design Deliverables**:
- Product detail page mockups (desktop, tablet, mobile)
- Image gallery interactions (zoom, lightbox, thumbnail navigation)
- Size guide modal design
- Add to cart success confirmation
- Error states (out of stock, no size selected)
- Related products section
- Expandable/accordion section designs
- Mobile sticky CTA design

---

#### Story UI-002.4: Search Interface

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** design an intuitive search experience with helpful suggestions,  
**So that** users can quickly find specific products or bands.

**Priority**: Must Have (MVP)  
**Estimated Effort**: 2 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am designing the search interface,  
**When** a user wants to search,  
**Then** the interface must include:
- Prominent search bar in header (visible on all pages)
- Search icon and placeholder text ("Search bands, designs...")
- Search dropdown with:
  - Recent searches (if returning user)
  - Popular searches/suggestions
  - Category suggestions
- Search results page with:
  - Search query display
  - Results count
  - Product grid matching listing page design
  - "No results" state with suggestions
  - Filters and sorting

**Given** I am enhancing usability,  
**When** a user types in the search bar,  
**Then** the design must:
- Show search suggestions dropdown (Phase 1: autocomplete)
- Highlight matching text in suggestions
- Support keyboard navigation (Arrow keys, Enter)
- Include clear button to reset search
- Display loading indicator while searching

**Design Deliverables**:
- Search bar designs (default, focused, with text)
- Search dropdown with suggestions
- Search results page mockups
- "No results" empty state with alternatives
- Mobile search interface (full-screen or overlay)

