### Epic: P3-002 - Accessibility & Dark Mode

#### Story P3-002.1: Dark Mode Design

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** design a dark mode theme,  
**So that** users can choose their preferred viewing mode and reduce eye strain.

**Priority**: Could Have (Phase 3)  
**Estimated Effort**: 3 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am designing dark mode,  
**When** a user enables dark mode,  
**Then** I must:
- Create complete dark color palette
- Maintain WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratios
- Design all pages in dark mode
- Include theme toggle (header or settings)
- Respect system preferences (prefers-color-scheme)
- Ensure images and media work in dark mode

**Design Deliverables**:
- Dark mode color system
- All pages designed in dark mode
- Theme toggle component
- Image/media optimization guidelines for dark mode

---

#### Story P3-002.2: WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance Audit

**As a** UI/UX Designer,  
**I want to** conduct a comprehensive accessibility audit,  
**So that** the site is usable by people with disabilities.

**Priority**: Should Have (Phase 3)  
**Estimated Effort**: 2 story points

**Acceptance Criteria**:

**Given** I am ensuring accessibility,  
**When** I audit the site,  
**Then** I must verify:
- Color contrast meets WCAG 2.1 AA (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large)
- All interactive elements have focus indicators
- Forms have proper labels and error announcements
- Images have alt text
- Headings create proper document structure
- Keyboard navigation works throughout
- Skip links are available
- ARIA labels are appropriate
- Touch targets are minimum 44x44px

**Design Deliverables**:
- Accessibility audit report
- Annotated mockups with ARIA labels
- Keyboard navigation flow diagram
- Focus indicator specifications
- Screen reader testing notes

---

